grades.title: SABIC® DPG_Dipropylene Glycol Regular Grade
grades.summary:
Chemical name	Oxybipropanol
Formula	C6H14O3
Molecular Weight (g/mol)	134.20
grades.description:
SABIC® DPG is a co-product from the manufacture of monopropylene glycol involving high temperature and high-pressure hydrolysis of propylene oxide (PO) with excess water. DPG is a high purity (99%) distilled product delivered in drum, IBC and bulk quantities.

DPG is a mixture of structural isomers (oxybispropanol CAS 25265-71-8, EINECS 246-770-3), defined by the manufacturing process and comprising: 
1,1'-oxybis-2-propanol (CAS 110-98-5, EINECS 203-821-4) 
2,2'-oxybis-1-propanol (CAS 108-61-2) 
2-(2-hydroxypropoxy)-1-propanol (CAS 106-62-7) 

DPG is a colorless, odorless, water soluble, medium viscosity and hygroscopic liquid with low vapor pressure and low toxicity.

grades.title: SABIC® TPG_Tripropylene Glycol Regular Grade
grades.summary:
Tripropylene Glycol (TPG), Chemical name	[(1-methyl-1,2-ethanediyl)(bis(oxy)]bispropanol
Formula	C9H20O4
Molecular Weight (g/mol)	192.30
grades.description:
SABIC® TPG is a co-product from the manufacture of monopropylene glycol involving high temperature and high-pressure hydrolysis of propylene oxide (PO) with excess water. TPG is a high purity distilled product delivered in drum, IBC and bulk quantities.

Our tightly controlled manufacturing process defines the consistent composition and isomer distribution of the product comprising the following isomers: 
1,1'-[(1-methyl-1,2-ethanediyl)bis(oxy)]bis-2-propanol (CAS 1638-16-0) (sec, sec-tripropylene glycol) 
2,2'-[(1-methyl-1,2-ethanediyl)bis(oxy)]bis-1-propanol (pri,pri-tripropylene glycol) 2-[1-(2-hydroxypropoxy)-2-propoxy]-1-propanol (pri, sec-tripropylene glycol) 
2-[2-(2-hydroxypropoxy)-propoxy]-1-propanol(CAS45096-22-8)(pri,sec-tripropylene glycol) 

TPG is a colorless, water soluble, medium viscosity, hygroscopic liquid with low vapor pressure, low toxicity and a faint glycol-specific odor.
